{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M83R3cFEyfyPKVycaCGwpi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three jobs completed successfully. Here's the summary:\n\n## Results\n\n### Job Status\nAll three Kubernetes jobs completed successfully (`Complete 1/1`):\n- `spark-skew-baseline` — 89s total duration\n- `spark-skew-broadcast` — 80s total duration\n- `spark-skew-aqe` — 78s total duration\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed (query) | Technique | Skew Handled |\n|----------|----------------|-----------|--------------|\n| **Baseline** | 25.58s | Standard shuffle join | No — 44x skew ratio |\n| **Broadcast Join** | 14.3s | Broadcast small table | Yes — no shuffle needed |\n| **AQE** | 14.2s | Auto split hot partitions | Yes — runtime adaptive |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n- **Skew ratio**: 44x — max partition had 11,579 rows vs min of 263 rows. The 5 hot products (product_id 1–5) each contributed 5,000 orders, creating massive straggler partitions.\n- **Broadcast join** reduced query time by ~44% (25.58s → 14.3s) by broadcasting the small `products` table to all executors, eliminating the skewed shuffle entirely.\n- **AQE** achieved nearly identical improvement (~44%, 25.58s → 14.2s) by detecting and automatically splitting the hot partitions at runtime — no schema changes required.\n\nBoth optimization strategies succeeded and the success criteria are met: baseline completed showing skew, and both broadcast and AQE optimizations were applied and completed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3002,"cache_read_input_tokens":29351,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3002},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"701f7131-3912-4057-9b9d-8b1bf14cb705","uu